---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Medical Banner Box — Danger
description: a medical record banner box for danger information (reactions, warnings, alarms)
---

{% from "components/medical-banner-box-for-danger/macro.njk" import medicalBannerBoxForDanger %}

<h2>Allergies</h2>
{{ medicalBannerBoxForDanger({
  heading: "Allergies",
  text: "Penicillin — rash, hives."
}) }}

<h2>Do Not Attempt CPR</h2>
{{ medicalBannerBoxForDanger({
  heading: "DNACPR",
  text: "Active since 10 April 2026."
}) }}

<h2>Multiple alerts</h2>
{% call medicalBannerBoxForDanger({ heading: "Safety alerts" }) %}
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
    <li>Penicillin allergy</li>
    <li>Fall risk — use bedrails</li>
    <li>NEWS2 score 5 (12:00)</li>
  </ul>
{% endcall %}

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>The macro sets <code>role="alert"</code> so assistive tech
  announces the contents when they appear. Use for patient-wide
  safety flags that must be persistently visible.</p>
